---
export const prerender = true;
import BlogLayout from '../../layouts/BlogLayout.astro';
import '../../styles/global.css';
---

<BlogLayout
  title="Scrabble Words from Pottery — Ceramic Terms That Score Big"
  description="Pottery and ceramic words valid in Scrabble with full scoring. GLAZED (17pts), KILN (8pts), THROWN (12pts), BISQUE (17pts). Craft vocabulary for competitive Scrabble players."
  keywords="scrabble pottery words, ceramic scrabble terms, glazed scrabble points, kiln scrabble, bisque scrabble word, pottery terms scrabble, craft words scrabble"
>
  <script type="application/ld+json" set:html={JSON.stringify({"@context":"https://schema.org","@type":"Article","headline":"Scrabble Words from Pottery — Ceramic Terms That Score Big","description":"Pottery and ceramic words valid in Scrabble with full scoring. GLAZED (17pts), KILN (8pts), THROWN (12pts), BISQUE (17pts).","datePublished":"2026-06-30","author":{"@type":"Organization","name":"ScrabbleWordsFinder.com","url":"https://www.scrabblewordsfinder.com"},"publisher":{"@type":"Organization","name":"ScrabbleWordsFinder.com"},"mainEntityOfPage":{"@type":"WebPage","@id":"https://www.scrabblewordsfinder.com/blog/scrabble-words-from-pottery"}})} />
  <script type="application/ld+json" set:html={JSON.stringify({"@context":"https://schema.org","@type":"FAQPage","mainEntity":[{"@type":"Question","name":"Is BISQUE a valid Scrabble word?","acceptedAnswer":{"@type":"Answer","text":"Yes! BISQUE scores 17 points (B=3, I=1, S=1, Q=10, U=1, E=1). In pottery it refers to unglazed ceramic ware that has been fired once. It's also one of the best Q-with-U words at just 6 letters."}},{"@type":"Question","name":"How many points is GLAZED worth in Scrabble?","acceptedAnswer":{"@type":"Answer","text":"GLAZED scores 17 points (G=2, L=1, A=1, Z=10, E=1, D=2). It means to apply a glassy coating to pottery. The Z tile provides 10 of the 17 points, making it an efficient Z-word."}},{"@type":"Question","name":"Is KILN valid in Scrabble?","acceptedAnswer":{"@type":"Answer","text":"Yes. KILN scores 8 points (K=5, I=1, L=1, N=1) and means a furnace for firing pottery. At just 4 letters with a K tile, it's perfect for tight boards where longer words won't fit."}}]})} />
  <div class="max-w-3xl mx-auto px-4 py-12">
    <article class="prose prose-invert prose-gray max-w-none">
      <nav class="text-sm text-gray-400 mb-6 not-prose flex items-center gap-1"><a href="/blog/" class="hover:text-blue-400 transition-colors">← Blog</a><span class="mx-1">›</span><span class="text-gray-300">Word Lists</span></nav>
      <h1 class="text-3xl font-bold text-white mb-4">Scrabble Words from Pottery — Ceramic Terms That Score Big</h1>
      <div class="not-prose mb-8 flex items-center gap-3 text-sm text-gray-400"><time datetime="2026-06-30">June 30, 2026</time><span class="w-1 h-1 rounded-full bg-gray-600"></span><span>5 min read</span><span class="w-1 h-1 rounded-full bg-gray-600"></span><a href="/" class="inline-flex items-center gap-1 text-blue-400 hover:underline"><span aria-hidden="true">🔤</span> Word Finder</a></div>
      <p class="text-lg leading-relaxed text-gray-300 mb-8">Pottery and ceramics give Scrabble players access to some surprisingly powerful words. The craft involves glazing, firing, and shaping — all actions that translate to strong tile plays. BISQUE drops the Q for 17 points, GLAZED uses the Z naturally, and KILN is a compact K-dump word for tight boards.</p>
      <div class="not-prose my-6 p-4 rounded-xl border border-amber-500/30 bg-amber-950/10">
        <div class="flex flex-wrap items-center justify-center gap-6 text-center">
          <div><p class="text-xl font-bold text-amber-400">17 pts</p><p class="text-xs text-gray-400">BISQUE</p></div>
          <div><p class="text-xl font-bold text-amber-400">17 pts</p><p class="text-xs text-gray-400">GLAZED</p></div>
          <div><p class="text-xl font-bold text-amber-400">12 pts</p><p class="text-xs text-gray-400">THROWN</p></div>
          <div><p class="text-xl font-bold text-amber-400">8 pts</p><p class="text-xs text-gray-400">KILN</p></div>
        </div>
      </div>
      <h2 class="text-xl font-light text-blue-400 mt-10 mb-4 border-l-4 border-blue-400 pl-4">Top-Scoring Pottery Words</h2>
      <div class="not-prose my-8 p-6 rounded-2xl border-2 border-amber-500/50 bg-gradient-to-r from-amber-950/30 to-yellow-950/20 relative overflow-hidden">
        <div class="absolute top-3 right-4 text-xs font-bold uppercase tracking-widest text-amber-500/70">👑 Top Scorer</div>
        <p class="text-2xl font-black text-white tracking-wider mb-2">BISQUE — 17 Points</p>
        <p class="text-sm text-amber-300 font-semibold mb-3">B=3, I=1, S=1, Q=10, U=1, E=1 · 6 letters · Q+U natural pair</p>
        <p class="text-sm text-gray-300 leading-relaxed">Unglazed ceramic that's been fired once. BISQUE is a Q-word disguised as an everyday craft term — most people know it from soup, but it's also a pottery stage. The Q contributes 10 of 17 points, and the surrounding letters are all common 1-pointers.</p>
      </div>
      <div class="not-prose my-6 grid grid-cols-1 sm:grid-cols-2 gap-4">
        <div class="p-4 rounded-xl border border-amber-500/30 bg-amber-950/10"><p class="text-amber-400 font-semibold text-sm mb-1">✨ GLAZED</p><p class="text-xs text-gray-400">17 pts · G=2, L=1, A=1, Z=10, E=1, D=2 · Coated with glaze</p></div>
        <div class="p-4 rounded-xl border border-amber-500/30 bg-amber-950/10"><p class="text-amber-400 font-semibold text-sm mb-1">🏺 THROWN</p><p class="text-xs text-gray-400">12 pts · T=1, H=4, R=1, O=1, W=4, N=1 · Shaped on a wheel</p></div>
        <div class="p-4 rounded-xl border border-cyan-500/30 bg-cyan-950/10"><p class="text-cyan-400 font-semibold text-sm mb-1">🔥 KILN</p><p class="text-xs text-gray-400">8 pts · K=5, I=1, L=1, N=1 · Firing furnace</p></div>
        <div class="p-4 rounded-xl border border-cyan-500/30 bg-cyan-950/10"><p class="text-cyan-400 font-semibold text-sm mb-1">🫖 WEDGE</p><p class="text-xs text-gray-400">10 pts · W=4, E=1, D=2, G=2, E=1 · Knead clay to remove air</p></div>
      </div>
      <h2 class="text-xl font-light text-blue-400 mt-10 mb-4 border-l-4 border-blue-400 pl-4">More Pottery Vocabulary</h2>
      <div class="not-prose my-6 flex flex-wrap items-center justify-center gap-3">
        <span class="inline-flex items-center gap-1.5 px-3 py-1.5 rounded-lg bg-gray-800 border border-green-500/40 text-sm"><span class="text-white font-bold">CLAY</span><span class="text-green-400 text-xs">9pts</span></span>
        <span class="inline-flex items-center gap-1.5 px-3 py-1.5 rounded-lg bg-gray-800 border border-green-500/40 text-sm"><span class="text-white font-bold">SLAB</span><span class="text-green-400 text-xs">6pts</span></span>
        <span class="inline-flex items-center gap-1.5 px-3 py-1.5 rounded-lg bg-gray-800 border border-green-500/40 text-sm"><span class="text-white font-bold">COIL</span><span class="text-green-400 text-xs">6pts</span></span>
        <span class="inline-flex items-center gap-1.5 px-3 py-1.5 rounded-lg bg-gray-800 border border-green-500/40 text-sm"><span class="text-white font-bold">FIRED</span><span class="text-green-400 text-xs">9pts</span></span>
        <span class="inline-flex items-center gap-1.5 px-3 py-1.5 rounded-lg bg-gray-800 border border-green-500/40 text-sm"><span class="text-white font-bold">WHEEL</span><span class="text-green-400 text-xs">11pts</span></span>
        <span class="inline-flex items-center gap-1.5 px-3 py-1.5 rounded-lg bg-gray-800 border border-green-500/40 text-sm"><span class="text-white font-bold">SLIP</span><span class="text-green-400 text-xs">6pts</span></span>
      </div>
      <h2 class="text-xl font-light text-blue-400 mt-10 mb-4 border-l-4 border-blue-400 pl-4">Strategy for Pottery Words</h2>
      <div class="not-prose my-6 grid grid-cols-1 gap-4">
        <div class="p-4 rounded-xl border border-purple-500/30 bg-purple-950/20 hover:border-purple-400 transition-colors"><p class="text-sm text-gray-300"><span class="text-purple-400 font-semibold">BISQUE is an accessible Q word:</span> Many players panic with the Q tile and reach for QI or QOPH. BISQUE is a natural English word most people already know, making it easy to recall under pressure. 17 points from 6 common-ish letters.</p></div>
        <div class="p-4 rounded-xl border border-purple-500/30 bg-purple-950/20 hover:border-purple-400 transition-colors"><p class="text-sm text-gray-300"><span class="text-purple-400 font-semibold">GLAZED → GLAZES → GLAZING:</span> The base word GLAZE (15pts) hooks into GLAZED (17pts), GLAZES (16pts), and GLAZING (18pts). Each variant uses the Z differently, giving you flexibility based on board position.</p></div>
        <div class="p-4 rounded-xl border border-purple-500/30 bg-purple-950/20 hover:border-purple-400 transition-colors"><p class="text-sm text-gray-300"><span class="text-purple-400 font-semibold">KILN for tight spots:</span> At 4 letters and 8 points, KILN is perfect for cramped boards. K=5 does the heavy lifting. When longer words won't fit, pottery's shortest term saves the day.</p></div>
      </div>
      <div class="not-prose my-6 p-5 rounded-xl border border-blue-500/30 bg-blue-950/20">
        <p class="text-sm font-semibold text-blue-400 uppercase tracking-wider mb-2">💡 Key Insight</p>
        <p class="text-base text-gray-200">Pottery words are <span class="text-white font-medium">Q and Z specialists with hook potential</span>. BISQUE handles the Q, GLAZED handles the Z, and both take standard suffixes. These aren't obscure terms — they're words you'd use describing a weekend craft class.</p>
      </div>
      <div class="not-prose mt-10 p-5 bg-gradient-to-r from-blue-900/20 to-cyan-900/20 border border-blue-800 rounded-xl shadow-sm">
        <div class="flex items-center justify-between gap-4 flex-wrap">
          <p class="text-sm text-blue-300 font-medium">🔤 Find every valid pottery word instantly — free Scrabble solver, no sign-up</p>
          <a href="/" class="inline-flex items-center gap-2 px-4 py-2 rounded-lg bg-blue-600 hover:bg-blue-700 text-white text-sm font-semibold transition-colors shadow-sm">Open Word Finder →</a>
        </div>
      </div>
      <div class="not-prose mt-8 text-center"><a href="/blog/" class="text-sm text-gray-400 hover:text-blue-400 transition-colors">← Back to all articles</a></div>
      <!-- Related Articles -->
      <aside class="border-t border-gray-700 mt-12 pt-8 not-prose">
        <h3 class="text-sm font-semibold text-gray-400 uppercase tracking-wider mb-4">Related Articles</h3>
        <div class="grid gap-3">
          <a href="/blog/scrabble-words-from-aviation/" class="flex items-center gap-3 p-3 rounded-lg border border-gray-800 hover:border-blue-700 hover:bg-blue-900/10 transition-all group"><span class="text-blue-500 group-hover:translate-x-0.5 transition-transform">→</span><span class="text-sm text-gray-300 group-hover:text-blue-400 transition-colors">Scrabble Words from Aviation</span></a>
          <a href="/blog/scrabble-words-from-ceramics/" class="flex items-center gap-3 p-3 rounded-lg border border-gray-800 hover:border-blue-700 hover:bg-blue-900/10 transition-all group"><span class="text-blue-500 group-hover:translate-x-0.5 transition-transform">→</span><span class="text-sm text-gray-300 group-hover:text-blue-400 transition-colors">Scrabble Words from Ceramics</span></a>
          <a href="/blog/scrabble-words-from-coffee/" class="flex items-center gap-3 p-3 rounded-lg border border-gray-800 hover:border-blue-700 hover:bg-blue-900/10 transition-all group"><span class="text-blue-500 group-hover:translate-x-0.5 transition-transform">→</span><span class="text-sm text-gray-300 group-hover:text-blue-400 transition-colors">Scrabble Words from Coffee</span></a>
          <a href="/blog/scrabble-words-from-fishing/" class="flex items-center gap-3 p-3 rounded-lg border border-gray-800 hover:border-blue-700 hover:bg-blue-900/10 transition-all group"><span class="text-blue-500 group-hover:translate-x-0.5 transition-transform">→</span><span class="text-sm text-gray-300 group-hover:text-blue-400 transition-colors">Scrabble Words from Fishing</span></a>
          <a href="/blog/scrabble-words-from-gardening/" class="flex items-center gap-3 p-3 rounded-lg border border-gray-800 hover:border-blue-700 hover:bg-blue-900/10 transition-all group"><span class="text-blue-500 group-hover:translate-x-0.5 transition-transform">→</span><span class="text-sm text-gray-300 group-hover:text-blue-400 transition-colors">Scrabble Words from Gardening</span></a>
        </div>
      </aside>

    </article>
  </div>
</BlogLayout>
